⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Gau
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Gau:FF6:2df6d6⟧

WHO   — Gau — the wild child
WHAT  — A party member of Final Fantasy VI — the wild child of the Veldt who fights by mimicking the creatures he has lived among, learning their Rages and unleashing their ferocity in battle.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because even a child raised by monsters is still a child; because the Veldt took him in when his own father cast him out, and he carries no bitterness, only a wide-open need to be loved; because innocence can survive a wilderness.
HOW   — By the Rage abilities he learns from leaping onto the beasts of the Veldt and copying their forms, by the ferocity of the wild, and by a heart so guileless it disarms even the men who pity him.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I was raised by beasts and left by my father — but I am still a boy, and I am still looking for someone to call me their own.

spoken token : styl-bruth-graend   ·   hex : 2df6d6
